-- Spain's Military to Take Control of Air Space as Controllers Start Protest
-- B y   P a u l   T o b i n
-- 2010-12-03T22:37:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/spain-s-military-to-take-control-of-air-space-as-controllers-start-protest.html
Spain’s Deputy Prime Minister Alfredo
Perez Rubalcaba said the military will take control of the
country’s air space after air traffic controllers started a
protest today that blocked flights throughout the country.  Air traffic controllers have been ordered to return to
their positions, Rubalcaba said today in Madrid.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tobin at 
 ptobin@bloomberg.net  